N2  - Postmenopausal bleeding is a common complaint among patients visiting a gynecologist and comprises nearly 5-10% of total patient turnover to a gynaecology clinic. Carugno stated that it is important to ascertain the exact cause of postmenopausal bleeding in order to understand the urgency of the situation and to offer appropriate treatment. Objective(s):To evaluate the leading causes of postmenopausal uterine bleeding among obese patients from 45-70 years. Conclusion(s):We concluded that the most common cause of postmenopausal bleeding is atrophy, either of the endometrium or the vaginal mucosa. Other common etiologies are endometrial hyperplasia, endometrial polyps, and submucousleiomyomas..Copyright © 2022, Anka Publishers. All rights reserved.
