T1  - The role of androgen excess in metabolic dysfunction in women: Androgen excess and female metabolic dysfunction
T2  - Advances in Experimental Medicine and Biology
A1  - Escobar-Morreale H.F. 
Y1  - 2017//
N2  - Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is characterized by the association of androgen excess with chronic oligoovulation and/or polycystic ovarian morphology, yet metabolic disorders and classic and nonclassic cardiovascular risk factors cluster in these women from very early in life. This chapter focuses on the mechanisms underlying the association of PCOS with metabolic dysfunction, focusing on the role of androgen excess on the development of visceral adiposity and adipose tissue dysfunction.Copyright © Springer International Publishing AG 2017.
