T1  - Preliminary two year results of the prospective multinational panacea trial on ParietexTM composite ventral patch in open primary ventral hernia repair
T3  - 18th Annual Hernia Repair. Cancun Mexico.
A1  - Doerhoff C.
A1  - Muysoms F.
A1  - Hopson S.
A1  - Muzi M.
A1  - Nienhuijs S.
A1  - Kullman E.
A1  - Tollens T.
A1  - Berrevoet F.
A1  - Jorgensen L. 
Y1  - 2017//
N2  - The ParietexTM Composite Ventral Patch (PCO-VP) is a monofilament composite mesh with absorbable expanders and four fixation points to assist with device positioning and fixation during open ventral hernia repair. The PANACEA trial is an ongoing prospective multinational non-comparative study to assess clinical outcomes with PCO-VP. Preliminary 24-months results and quality of life results are reported herein. Primary ventral hernias were repaired open with intraperitoneal placement of PCO-VP. Patients were clinically assessed at 1, 6, 12, and 24 months post-surgery for hernia recurrence and clinical outcomes. The primary endpoint is recurrence within 24 months. 126 ventral hernia patients with a mean hernia diameter of 1.8 +/- 0.8 cm were treated with PCO-VP. At this interim analysis, 110 patients completed 12 months follow-up, and 32 patients completed the two year study. Median time to return to work was 11.0 days (range 1.0-48.0) and time to return to playing sports was 10.0 days (2.0-55.0). Numeric Rating Scale pain scores (0 = min, 10 = max) were significantly reduced at 1 month (-1.6 +/- 2.0, p<0.001), 12 months (-1.9 +/- 1.9, p<0.001) and 24 months (-1.9 +/- 1.5, p<0.001) compared to preoperative levels. The mean global Carolina'sTM Comfort Scale score improved from 3.8 +/- 6.2 at 1 month post-surgery to 2.4 +/- 7.7 (p = 0.03) at 24 months postsurgery. At 1 month, movement limitation scores (0 no symptom; 5 disabling) were 0.2 +/- 0.4 while performing normal daily activities, coughing, or deep breathing, and were 0.2 +/- 0.5 while exercising. Cumulative hernia recurrence rates within 6 and 12 months were 1.8% (2/114) and 2.8% (3/106), respectively. The PANACEA results show promisingly low recurrence rates. Pain and QOL scores are acceptable at 1 month and continue to improve through 24 months following primary open ventral hernia repair with PCO-VP.
